commit.message: Added in Nexmo messaging .
Updated README.md
Added in audio when sadness reached.
Updated SDK and config

Merge pull request #21 from Affectiva/3.2

3.2

remove revertPointRotation call in VideoDetectorDemo

no need to call RevertPointRotation; SDK now returns points in
upright orientation.

revert targetSdkVersion to avoid the need for runtime permission logic

VideoDetectorDemo needs access to the file system, but doesn't
yet have runtime permission support, so we can't set targetSdkVersion
higher than 22 for now.

ServiceFrameDetectorDemo has the runtime permission check, so
it uses 23.

3.2 SDK updates & other build misc

add UI for displaying brightness value in CameraDetectorDemo,
FrameDetectorDemo, and VideoDetectorDemo.

consolidate gradle stuff which is common to all modules in
module-defaults.gradle.  This simplified the module build.gradle files
considerably.

update affdexsdk dependencies for all sample apps to use dynamic versioning
with value of "3.+", which will cause them to pick up the highest-numbered
SDK release in the 3.x series.  This way we don't necessarily need to update the
samples when we do a point release.

update gradle plugin to 2.2.2

set all versionCode values to 1 (normally a Bad Thing if you're app is
published to the Play store, but these aren't, so simpler to just have it
this way)

set APK naming style to appname-version-build#

address timestamp precision issue in FrameDetectorDemo

FrameDetector Demo was sending epoch-based frame timestamps.  Due to the precision
limit of floats in Java and the large values of epoch-based  timestamps, this resulted in
imprecise values being delivered to the detector.  This commit changes the approach to
use first-frame-relative timestamps instead of epoch-relative values.
